As of the morning of the 27th, South Korea had only 1,077 negative pressure beds, far fewer than the number of confirmed cases.



As of 9:00 a.m. on February 28,256 new cases of coronavirus infection had been confirmed in South Korea, bringing the total to 2,022, with 13 deaths and 26 cured cases.

Of the 256 new cases, 182 were from Taegu and 49 from Qingbei. So far, in addition to confirmed cases, the cumulative total of 68,918 people tested for the virus in South Korea, 44,167 of whom tested negative, the remaining 24,751 results have not yet been released.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Source: Korea Central Epidemic Prevention Countermeasures Department

Currently, more than 80% of confirmed cases in South Korea are concentrated in the adjacent areas of Taegu and Gyeongbuk, with two major infectious sites respectively: the New World Taegu Church and gyeongbuk-do County Dannan Hospital.

Of the 2,022 confirmed cases as of 9 am, 1,314 and 394 cases were from Taegu and Qingbei regions, accounting for 65% and 19.5% respectively. Of the 1,595 confirmed cases as of 9:00 am, 731 cases were related to New World Church of Taegu and Qing Dao County da Nan hospital, accounting for 45.8% and 7.1% respectively.

South Korean health authorities since 26, about 210,000 New World Church believers have been tested. Currently, of the more than 9,000 followers of the new world church in Taegu, 1,299 cases of symptomatic cases have been collected and the number of new cases is expected to surge in the next two days, said Jeong eun-kyung, head of the central anti-epidemic measures department, on the 27th.

There has been no significant increase in the number of cases related to Dannan Hospital in recent days, with a total of 103 patients, 10 health care workers and 1 family member confirmed, but of the 13 deaths so far, seven cases were found in the hospital and four were related to the new World Church.

According to Yonhap reported on the 27th, with the increasing number of confirmed cases of new coronavirus infection in South Korea, private medical institutions in South Korea have opened negative pressure wards and other facilities to alleviate the shortage of negative pressure wards in state-designated medical institutions.

South Korea's largest private medical institution, Foshan Mount Seoul Hospital and Samsung Seoul hospital, opened 6 and 22 negative pressure wards for patients with newly diagnosed pneumonia, according to news from the medical sector on the same day. Yonsei University has decided to provide 22 negative pressure wards for new cases of pneumonia starting March 2, and Notre Dame in Seoul is also discussing the matter.

The East Asia daily pointed out earlier in the day that with the addition of private medical institutions, there are only 1,077 negative pressure beds for the isolation and treatment of infected persons in South Korea, which is far less than the cumulative number of confirmed cases, the strategy of allocating medical resources must be reformulated as soon as possible to prepare for a possible "protracted war" .

According to Yonhap News Agency reported that 27, the 13th death case is due to insufficient beds, while waiting to be hospitalized seriously ill.
